The paper focuses on understanding cultural phenomena on social networks and predicting future observations, which falls under the scope of social network analysis and information retrieval. The paper also mentions the use of semantic web constructs and methods, which suggests a connection to knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI) and web technologies (cs.WEB). However, since the paper specifically tests its framework on the computer science research community using the DBLP database, categories related to databases (cs.DB), digital libraries (cs.DL), and information retrieval (cs.IR) are more likely. Additionally, since the paper discusses the propagation of individual interests in social networks, categories related to social networks (cs.SOC) and social media (cs.SI) are also likely.
